<item>
            <title>[SPARK-27041] large partition data cause pyspark with python2.x oom</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-27041</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With large partition, pyspark may exceeds executor memory limit and trigger out of memory for python 2.7.&lt;br/&gt;
This is because map() is used. Unlike in python3.x, python 2.7 map() will generate a list and need to read all data into memory.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The proposed fix will use imap in python 2.7 and it has been verified.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
